 <h1>Qualifications/Disadvantages</h1>
 <p>Booker has a good grasp on laws, and what it takes to pass them. Because of his position as a Senator, he likely holds some sway over the Senate. He likely understands how to play the political game, and is “electable.” He has some high profile “wins,” a prime example being the bipartisan mostly well-liked First Step Act. Unfortunately, he also has his history of being a Senator that means that he might have more “dirty laundry” that can be used against him in his voting history. He would also be going against an incumbent and has yet to really distinguish himself in the public psyche. </p>


